<item>
            <title>[HBASE-10770] Don&apos;t exit from the Canary daemon mode if no regions are present</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-10770</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Using the regionserver mode the canary exit if there are no region servers&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;hbase o.a.h.h.tool.Canary -daemon -regionserver REGION_NAME&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;while in table mode the canary is waiting until the table is up&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;hbase o.a.h.h.tool.Canary -daemon TABLE_NAME&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Remove the exit code from the region server mode, and keep waiting until  the -t timeout or the region shows up&lt;/p&gt;</description>
